<h2>Galadriel</h2>
<div class="about-page">
  <div class="image">
    <img src="/images/Galadriel.jpg" alt="Galadriel" class="galadriel-image" />
  </div>

  <div class="about">
    <h3>Biography:</h3>
    <p>
      Galadriel was the Lade of the Woods of Lothlórien, which she rules with
      Celeborn, her husband. One of the greatest of the Elves in middle-earth,
      she surpassed nearly all other in beauty, knowledge and power. She bore
      Nenya, one of the three Elven rings of power.
    </p>
    <h3>Titles:</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Princess of the Ñoldor</li>
      <li>Lady of Lórien</li>
      <li>Lady of the Galadhrim</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Quotes:</h3>
    <p>
      "Do not be afraid, Mithrandir. You are not alone" Galadriel speaking to
      Gandalf after the one ring surfaces again during the journey of the
      dwarves to retake the Lonely Mountain
    </p>
    <p>
      "The world is changed" The first line spoken in the trilogy of movies. A
      perfect setup for the scenes about to unfold.
    </p>
    <p>
      "Do we leave Middle-earth to its fate? Do we let them stand alone?"
      Galadriel speaking with Elrond, and changing her mind on the exodus of the
      elves from Middle-earth.
    </p>
  </div>
